# Project Rules and Design Guidelines (MonFuturBoulot.com)

You must strictly adhere to the following UI, UX, and design system rules for all code modifications, new component additions, and page developments in this workspace.

---

## 1. Core Color Palette & Design Tokens

You must ONLY use the CSS variables defined in [globals.css](file:///Users/romeomoumouniattolou/Mon%20futur%20job/src/app/globals.css). Never hardcode generic hex values, RGB values, or color names.

### Brand Colors
- **Primary Brand Color**: `var(--primary)` (`#00b87c`)
- **Primary Hover**: `var(--primary-hover)` (`#009e6a`)
- **Primary Light (Background/Highlight)**: `var(--primary-light)` (`#e8f9f3`)
- **Primary Glow**: `var(--primary-glow)` (`rgba(0, 184, 124, 0.15)`)

### Dark Theme Palette
- **Background**: `var(--dark-bg)` (`#080c14`)
- **Card Background**: `var(--dark-card)` (`#0e1422`)
- **Border**: `var(--dark-border)` (`#1a2436`)
- **Text (High Contrast)**: `var(--dark-text)` (`#f8fafc`)
- **Text (Muted)**: `var(--dark-text-muted)` (`#94a3b8`)

### Light Theme Palette
- **Background**: `var(--light-bg)` (`#f8fafc`)
- **Card Background**: `var(--light-card)` (`#ffffff`)
- **Border**: `var(--light-border)` (`#e2e8f0`)
- **Text (High Contrast)**: `var(--light-text)` (`#0f172a`)
- **Text (Muted)**: `var(--light-text-muted)` (`#64748b`)

### Alert & Status Colors
- **Error**: `var(--error)` (`#ef4444`)
- **Success**: `var(--success)` (`#10b981`)
- **Warning**: `var(--warning)` (`#f59e0b`)

---

## 2. Layout, Borders & Shadows

- **Border Radius**:
  - Small elements (inputs, badges, small buttons): `var(--radius-sm)` (`8px`)
  - Medium elements (cards, containers, standard buttons): `var(--radius-md)` (`12px`)
  - Large elements (major pages section cards, modals): `var(--radius-lg)` (`18px`)
  - Pills, tags, full-round components: `var(--radius-full)` (`9999px`)
- **Shadows**:
  - Dropdown/menus: `var(--shadow-sm)`
  - Cards, default panels: `var(--shadow-md)`
  - Elevated modals/CV previews: `var(--shadow-lg)`
  - Premium sections: `var(--shadow-premium)`
- **Transitions**:
  - Always use `var(--transition)` (`all 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`) for hover states, color shifts, and transitions.

---

## 3. Typography & Styling Guidelines

- **Font Family**: Always use `'Outfit', sans-serif`. Do not use default sans-serif or other fonts.
- **Font Weights**:
  - Headings (h1, h2, h3, h4): `700` or `800` for strong prominence.
  - Subtitles and key UI labels: `500` or `600`.
  - Body text: `300` or `400`.
- **Text Gradients**: For premium headers and accents, use the `.text-gradient` helper:
  `background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, #00e699 100%);`
  `-webkit-background-clip: text;`
  `-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;`

---

## 4. Components & UX Standards

### Buttons
Use the predefined CSS classes in `.globals.css` or map inline styles to mirror:
- **Primary**: `.btn.btn-primary` (Green background, white text, transform hover + glow shadow)
- **Secondary**: `.btn.btn-secondary` (White background, dark text, light border)
- **Dark/Outline-Dark**: `.btn.btn-dark` or `.btn.btn-outline-dark`

### Forms & Inputs
All interactive inputs must use:
- Class `.form-input`
- High-contrast text, smooth focus borders in `var(--primary)`, and a subtle outer glow shadow using `var(--primary-glow)`.

### Theme Wrappers
Ensure pages have appropriate wrapper elements. E.g., for dark theme pages, use `<div className="dark-theme">` as a container to apply appropriate global dark background and text overrides.

### Language
All user-facing text, actions, and headings must be in **French** (fr) as per the project requirements.

---

## 5. 📱 Mobile-First Responsive Design — RÈGLE OBLIGATOIRE

> ⚠️ **AVANT toute modification UI, TOUJOURS vérifier le rendu mobile en premier (375px de large).**

### Breakpoints officiels
| Écran | Largeur | Comportement |
|---|---|---|
| Mobile | `< 768px` | 1 colonne, sidebar cachée, nav hamburger |
| Tablette | `768–1023px` | Grilles compactes, 2 colonnes max |
| Desktop | `≥ 1024px` | Sidebar fixe, multi-colonnes, layout complet |

### Règles de mise en page
- **Sidebar Dashboard** : sur mobile, c'est un panneau coulissant (`position: fixed`, `transform: translateX(-100%)`) déclenché par un bouton hamburger (`.db-hamburger`). Utiliser les classes CSS : `.db-sidebar`, `.db-sidebar.sidebar-open`, `.db-sidebar-overlay.overlay-active`.
- **Grids** : toujours utiliser les classes CSS dédiées au lieu d'inline styles pour les grilles multi-colonnes :
  - `.db-split` → 2 cols desktop, 1 col mobile
  - `.db-cv-workspace` → 2 cols desktop, 1 col mobile
  - `.db-pricing-grid` → 3 cols desktop, 1 col mobile
  - `.db-stats-grid` → auto-fit desktop, 2 cols mobile
- **Ne jamais** écrire `gridTemplateColumns: 'repeat(N, 1fr)'` sans ajouter la classe CSS responsive correspondante.
- **Tailles de police** : maximum `h1` sur mobile = `28px`. Utiliser la classe `.hero-title-responsive` pour les grands titres.
- **Boutons** : dans un formulaire ou en contexte hero, `width: 100%` sur mobile.
- **Padding** : utiliser `padding: 14px` sur mobile au lieu de `30px+`. La classe `.db-content` gère cela automatiquement.

### Classes CSS disponibles (dans `globals.css`)
- **Landing** : `.landing-nav`, `.landing-nav-actions`, `.landing-mobile-toggle`, `.hero-actions-row`, `.footer-grid-responsive`, `.footer-bottom-responsive`
- **Dashboard** : `.db-layout`, `.db-main`, `.db-sidebar`, `.db-sidebar-overlay`, `.db-hamburger`, `.db-sidebar-close`, `.db-content`, `.db-topbar-search`, `.db-user-meta`, `.db-welcome-btns`, `.db-split`, `.db-cv-workspace`, `.db-pricing-grid`, `.db-admin-stats`, `.db-admin-cols`, `.db-stats-grid`

### Checklist avant tout commit UI
- [ ] Testé à 375px (iPhone SE)
- [ ] Testé à 390px (iPhone 14)
- [ ] Testé à 768px (tablette)
- [ ] Sidebar hamburger fonctionne
- [ ] Pas de scroll horizontal
- [ ] Boutons et formulaires accessibles au pouce
